sentences: John Mayall, OBE (born 29 November 1933) is an English blues singer, guitarist, organist and songwriter, whose musical career spans over sixty years.
In the 1960s, he was the founder of John Mayall & the Bluesbreakers, a band which has counted among its members some of the most famous blues and blues rock musicians.
Born in Macclesfield, Cheshire in 1933, Mayall was the son of Murray Mayall, a guitarist and jazz music enthusiast.
In 1963, he opted for a full-time musical career and moved to London.
A brush fire destroyed his house in Laurel Canyon in 1979, seriously damaging his musical collections and archives.
